!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

map /mæp/

(mapping,mapped,maps) 

1. N-COUNT A map is a drawing of a particular area such as a city, a country, or a continent, showing its main features as they would appear if you looked at them from above. 地图 

例： He unfolded the map and set it on the floor. 他展开地图，把它放在了地板上。 

2. V-T To map an area means to make a map of it. 绘制…的地图 

例： ...a spacecraft which is using radar to map the surface of Venus. …一艘利用雷达绘制金星表面地图的航天器。

</div>

